The overall objective of this EC/SIDA funded initiative in Abkhazia and adjacent areas in western Georgia is to enhance stability and security through confidence building measures aiming at the prevention and settlement of internal conflicts and actions in favour of affected populations. It aims to create preconditions for local economic and social development, as well as for safe and dignified repatriation of refugees and displaced persons.
The specific objectives of the project are:
1/ To further enhance the access to education through the rehabilitation of schools, provision of equipment, and the training and capacity building of school teachers, other education professionals and administrators;
2/ To further enhance the delivery of and the access to social services through rehabilitation of health care facilities, provision of equipment, and the training and capacity building of medical professionals, other healthcare staff and administrators;
3/ To further improve the infrastructure through the rehabilitation of the water supplies and the capacity building of water operators and administrative staff responsible for water management;
4/ To increase confidence building between various communities and between communities and returnees and/or IDPs.
The project is funded by EC, SIDA is financing international project manager's costs.

